<TITLE> Delwar slams AL for 'continued post-polls attacks' </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 Dhaka, Jan 10 (bdnews24.com)  BNP general secretary Khandaker Delwar Hossain has expressed concern over the continuation of post-election 'violence and terrorism'. In a statement, he said, "On one side the terrorists of the ruling party are attacking BNP workers and leaders and, on the other, the ministers are patronising terrorists." He feared the country may become a haven for terrorists if the violence went on. Delwar asked the ruling Awami League to reject terrorism and respect democracy. The statement claimed on Jan. 9, after BNP chief Khaleda Zia's speech at Chatkhil, Noakhali, AL terrorists attacked BNP rallies. "Despite criticism from different quarters, AL did not stop terrorist acts," alleged Delwar. The secretary general also pointed at attacks on BNP workers and leaders in Kendua upazila in Netrokona and Char Fashion in Bhola. As a result of these attacks, people had been forced to leave their homes, he added. b
